    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cabinets for storing wine, usually located near the dining table, having four or more openings for bottles, often with ice to cool the wine. The type is particularly well known in Tuscany.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
